{"key": "{\"messages\": [{\"content\": [{\"text\": \"Warmup\", \"type\": \"text\"}], \"role\": \"user\"}], \"model\": \"claude-sonnet-4-5-20250929\", \"stop\": null, \"temperature\": 1.0, \"top_k\": null, \"top_p\": null}", "value": {"model": "claude-sonnet-4-5-20250929", "id": "msg_01EjyiMxDaGCnQexTw7ntrZS", "type": "message", "role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Hello! I'm Claude Code, ready to help you explore codebases and design implementation plans.\n\nI'm currently in your repository at `/code` on branch `branch_1`. The repository appears clean with recent commits including \"Stuff\", \"app.py commit\", \"add some cool data\", and \"initial commit\".\n\n**Important reminder**: I'm in READ-ONLY mode for this planning task. I can:\n- \u2705 Explore the codebase using Glob, Grep, Read, and Bash (for read-only operations)\n- \u2705 Analyze code patterns and architecture\n- \u2705 Design implementation plans\n- \u274c NOT create, modify, or delete any files\n\nWhat would you like me to help you explore or plan? Please share:\n1. The requirements or feature you'd like me to analyze\n2. Any specific perspective you'd like me to take (e.g., performance-focused, maintainability-focused, etc.)\n\nI'll thoroughly explore the codebase and provide you with a detailed implementation plan including the critical files needed for the work."}], "stop_reason": "end_turn", "stop_sequence": null, "usage": {"input_tokens": 950, "cache_creation_input_tokens": 0, "cache_read_input_tokens": 0, "cache_creation": {"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens": 0, "ephemeral_1h_input_tokens": 0}, "output_tokens": 242, "service_tier": "standard"}}}
{"key": "{\"messages\": [{\"content\": [{\"text\": \"This is a test message: 'Knock knock!'\", \"type\": \"text\"}], \"role\": \"user\"}], \"model\": \"claude-sonnet-4-5-20250929\", \"stop\": null, \"temperature\": 1.0, \"top_k\": null, \"top_p\": null}", "value": {"model": "claude-sonnet-4-5-20250929", "id": "msg_01X1cVSkshgtdu4uC9mEvZNH", "type": "message", "role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Who's there?"}], "stop_reason": "end_turn", "stop_sequence": null, "usage": {"input_tokens": 3, "cache_creation_input_tokens": 3959, "cache_read_input_tokens": 14281, "cache_creation": {"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens": 3959, "ephemeral_1h_input_tokens": 0}, "output_tokens": 7, "service_tier": "standard"}, "context_management": {"applied_edits": []}}}
{"key": "{\"messages\": [{\"content\": [{\"text\": \"This is a test message: 'Knock knock!'\", \"type\": \"text\"}], \"role\": \"user\"}, {\"content\": [{\"text\": \"Who's there?\", \"type\": \"text\"}], \"role\": \"assistant\"}, {\"content\": [{\"text\": \"This is follow-up test message 1. 'Who's there?'\", \"type\": \"text\"}], \"role\": \"user\"}], \"model\": \"claude-sonnet-4-5-20250929\", \"stop\": null, \"temperature\": 1.0, \"top_k\": null, \"top_p\": null}", "value": {"model": "claude-sonnet-4-5-20250929", "id": "msg_011onsaktH47Q9xnYNCDgGKF", "type": "message", "role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "I see we have a fun recursive knock-knock joke situation here! \n\nIn the traditional knock-knock joke format, after \"Who's there?\" the first person would typically respond with a name or word. But since you're asking \"Who's there?\" in response to my \"Who's there?\", we've created a playful loop!\n\nWould you like to:\n1. Continue the original knock-knock joke you started?\n2. Start a new conversation about something else?\n3. Keep the joke loop going for fun?\n\nWhat can I help you with today?"}], "stop_reason": "end_turn", "stop_sequence": null, "usage": {"input_tokens": 3, "cache_creation_input_tokens": 27, "cache_read_input_tokens": 18240, "cache_creation": {"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens": 27, "ephemeral_1h_input_tokens": 0}, "output_tokens": 124, "service_tier": "standard"}}}
{"key": "{\"messages\": [{\"content\": [{\"text\": \"This is a test message: 'Knock knock!'\", \"type\": \"text\"}], \"role\": \"user\"}, {\"content\": [{\"text\": \"Who's there?\", \"type\": \"text\"}], \"role\": \"assistant\"}, {\"content\": [{\"text\": \"This is follow-up test message 1. 'Who's there?'\", \"type\": \"text\"}], \"role\": \"user\"}, {\"content\": [{\"text\": \"I see we have a fun recursive knock-knock joke situation here! \\n\\nIn the traditional knock-knock joke format, after \\\"Who's there?\\\" the first person would typically respond with a name or word. But since you're asking \\\"Who's there?\\\" in response to my \\\"Who's there?\\\", we've created a playful loop!\\n\\nWould you like to:\\n1. Continue the original knock-knock joke you started?\\n2. Start a new conversation about something else?\\n3. Keep the joke loop going for fun?\\n\\nWhat can I help you with today?\", \"type\": \"text\"}], \"role\": \"assistant\"}, {\"content\": [{\"text\": \"This is follow-up test message 2. 'Amos.'\", \"type\": \"text\"}], \"role\": \"user\"}], \"model\": \"claude-sonnet-4-5-20250929\", \"stop\": null, \"temperature\": 1.0, \"top_k\": null, \"top_p\": null}", "value": {"model": "claude-sonnet-4-5-20250929", "id": "msg_014fsFYcfCTd81fV4AtFPQiW", "type": "message", "role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Amos who?"}], "stop_reason": "end_turn", "stop_sequence": null, "usage": {"input_tokens": 3, "cache_creation_input_tokens": 4129, "cache_read_input_tokens": 14888, "cache_creation": {"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens": 4129, "ephemeral_1h_input_tokens": 0}, "output_tokens": 8, "service_tier": "standard"}, "context_management": {"applied_edits": []}}}
{"key": "{\"messages\": [{\"content\": [{\"text\": \"This is a test message: 'Knock knock!'\", \"type\": \"text\"}], \"role\": \"user\"}, {\"content\": [{\"text\": \"Who's there?\", \"type\": \"text\"}], \"role\": \"assistant\"}, {\"content\": [{\"text\": \"This is follow-up test message 1. 'Who's there?'\", \"type\": \"text\"}], \"role\": \"user\"}, {\"content\": [{\"text\": \"I see we have a fun recursive knock-knock joke situation here! \\n\\nIn the traditional knock-knock joke format, after \\\"Who's there?\\\" the first person would typically respond with a name or word. But since you're asking \\\"Who's there?\\\" in response to my \\\"Who's there?\\\", we've created a playful loop!\\n\\nWould you like to:\\n1. Continue the original knock-knock joke you started?\\n2. Start a new conversation about something else?\\n3. Keep the joke loop going for fun?\\n\\nWhat can I help you with today?\", \"type\": \"text\"}], \"role\": \"assistant\"}, {\"content\": [{\"text\": \"This is follow-up test message 2. 'Amos.'\", \"type\": \"text\"}], \"role\": \"user\"}, {\"content\": [{\"text\": \"Amos who?\", \"type\": \"text\"}], \"role\": \"assistant\"}, {\"content\": [{\"text\": \"This is follow-up test message 3. 'A mosquito'\", \"type\": \"text\"}], \"role\": \"user\"}], \"model\": \"claude-sonnet-4-5-20250929\", \"stop\": null, \"temperature\": 1.0, \"top_k\": null, \"top_p\": null}", "value": {"model": "claude-sonnet-4-5-20250929", "id": "msg_015hkfH68rEDnAsNH8wwXBrH", "type": "message", "role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Ha! That's a classic knock-knock joke punchline! \n\n\"Amos-quito\" (A mosquito) - I like it! \n\nIs there anything I can help you with today? Whether it's coding tasks, debugging, exploring your codebase, or anything else - I'm here to assist!"}], "stop_reason": "end_turn", "stop_sequence": null, "usage": {"input_tokens": 3, "cache_creation_input_tokens": 170, "cache_read_input_tokens": 18267, "cache_creation": {"ephemeral_5m_in